{"timestamp": "2025-11-28 14:50:29.105250", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission recorded.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"host_1_1_1_1\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"host_incorrect_netmask\"]\n\nRecommended remediation (apply on host_1_1_1_1):\n- Correct the netmask to /24 (255.255.255.0) so the host uses its default gateway for remote 10.x networks.\n  Example commands (Linux):\n  - ip addr add 10.1.1.2/24 dev eth0 (or: ip addr change 10.1.1.2/24 dev eth0)\n  - ip route replace default via 10.1.1.1\n- Verify:\n  - ip addr show eth0 (should show 10.1.1.2/24)\n  - ip route (should not show 10.0.0.0/8 on-link; default via 10.1.1.1 present)\n  - arp -n (should no longer ARP for remote 10.200.0.x addresses)\n  - ping 10.200.0.2 (DNS) and a web server to confirm reachability.\n\nIf you want, I can produce the exact CLI sequence for your host OS or run extra checks (live ARP/ping traces) to confirm the fix.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2044, "output_tokens": 285, "total_tokens": 2329, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1664}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
